article.headline: Bucknell 64, Navy 55
article.story: LEWISBURG, Pa. -- Mike Muscala scored 19 points and Bucknell defeated Navy 64-55 on Saturday, giving the Midshipmen their 20th loss in a row. Muscala was 6 of 8 from the field and 7 of 7 from the free-throw line as the Bison (22-8, 12-2 Patriot League) made 21 of 24 foul shots. Navy (3-25, 0-14) shot just 58.3 percent from the line (7 of 12), and didn't do much better from the field. The Midshipmen made 38.9 percent from the floor (21 of 54) and were just 6 of 22 from 3-point range. Joe Willman added 12 points and Ben Brackney had 10, as two of 10 scorers for Bucknell, which outrebounded Navy 36-24. The Bison led 28-17 after limiting Navy to 1 of 11 from 3-point range. Isaiah Roberts scored 19 points and Jordan Sugars added 13 points for the Midshipmen.
